Proponents

Violeta Chapetón

Violeta Chapetón

Violeta Chapetón Chura is a Bolivian politician who is currently the governor of the Cochabamba Province. She has previously served as the president of the regional government or prefect, chaired the legislative committees on health and education, and been a member of Parliament. She led the campaign for abortion.

Chapeton is from Bolivia's mustard-green MAS (Movement Towards Socialism) party, but diverges on this issue from her party support of decriminalization.
